						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the image of Gaṇēśa in the first enclosure of the Sōmanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Virūpāksha, 1486 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 140[7]</hi> (expired), <hi rend="bold">Parābhava, Kārttika śu. 1,</hi> (Saturday), corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1486 A.D., October 28.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a grant of income from taxes like the salt tax, <hi rend="italic">sāladeṟe</hi> etc., to the god Mūrukēriya Sōmanāthadēva by <hi rend="bold">Virupākshaoḍeya.</hi> The record is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
